There is a &quot;[maven git plugin][1]&quot; that gives some information over the commit. And this plugin has a property for specifying where is the .git directory:

    &lt;dotGitDirectory&gt;${project.basedir}/.git&lt;/dotGitDirectory&gt;


In your case, you have a multi-module structure. If you access this property in one of your sub-modules it will give you the base dir of the sub-project instead of the &quot;parent&quot; (unless you use absolute paths).

You can create a property in each sub-module to do the same thing (assuming that *.git* is in your parent module):

      &lt;properties&gt;
        &lt;vcs.root.path&gt;${basedir}/../.git
        &lt;/vcs.root.path&gt;
      &lt;/properties&gt;


  [1]: https://github.com/git-commit-id/git-commit-id-maven-plugin

